        - <span>WORLD IN PICTURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Ja­panese mambo mu­si­cian Par­adise Ya­mamoto has been a Santa for 23 years.</p>
    <p>He wants to re­as­sure chil­dren that Santa is still com­ing to their houses this Christ­mas.</p>
    <p>“I’ve never heard of a Christ­mas where Santa Claus didn’t ap­pear,” said the 58-year-old, who also owns a gy­oza restau­rant, where he works as a chef. “I might try to get in your houses through a dif­fer­ent route from usual, but I will most cer­tainly visit ev­ery­one’s homes – af­ter, of course, wash­ing my hands, gar­gling, dis­in­fect­ing the soles of my shoes, and tak­ing the proper mea­sures to pre­vent the spread of the coro­n­avirus.”</p>

